Key Match Events: Liam Livingstone smashed six fours and five sixes in a match-winning knock of 87 for England against Australia in Cardiff.
Travis Head hit a brisk 31 as he led from the front and also watched Jake Fraser-McGurk crash his maiden international half-century.
England levelled the T20 international series with a thrilling three-wicket victory at Cardiff.
Captain Phil Salt hit three successive sixes in the third over before Sean Abbott pegged England back with two quick wickets in the fourth.
Salt went for 39 off 23 balls, caught by Abbott.
Livingstone's tremendous partnership with Jacob Bethell (44 from 24) steadied the hosts and set them on the path to victory.
Livingstone took England to the brink with a six and a four but was then caught by Matt Short with one run required, leaving Adil Rashid to close the game out with a single and six balls remaining.
Part-time spinner Matt Short took 5-22 off three overs.
